               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410823-name-1204" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1204" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1204" type="surname" value="MEADOWS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1204" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS MEADOWS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am journeyman to Joseph Jackson, a baker, in Tooley-street. On the 18th of August I left my basket and bread at the corner of William-street, Hampstead-road—I went to Mornington-place to serve a customer—I returned in six or eight minutes, and missed twelve 2lb. loaves, and one 4lb. loaf—I went up William-street, and found the prisoner's basket standing at the door of a doctor's shop, and found it con<lb></lb>tained my bread—I stopped there about two minutes—the prisoner was coming down the street with a man holding his collar, with the 4lb. loaf under his arm—I could swear to the bread—it was my make.</p>
